{"_type":"issue","id":"prism-4gf.37","title":"[prism-self-review] exit-code uses identity match; Decision needs ordering for fail_on","description":"Found by Prism. main() returns 1 only if decision IS policy.fail_on (exact identity). For a non-default fail_on (e.g. minor_issues), a more severe significant_concerns would NOT fail CI. Fix: give Decision a severity ordering and compare 'decision \u003e= fail_on'.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"joshuafuller@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-29T18:14:02Z","created_by":"Joshua Fuller","updated_at":"2026-05-29T18:30:01Z","started_at":"2026-05-29T18:29:02Z","closed_at":"2026-05-29T18:30:01Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"prism-4gf.37","depends_on_id":"prism-4gf","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-05-29T13:14:02Z","created_by":"Joshua Fuller","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"prism-4gf.36","title":"[prism-self-review] cli drops fanout.skipped (silent reviewer loss)","description":"Found by Prism reviewing its own code. run_local_review uses fanout.findings but ignores fanout.skipped, so a timed-out/errored reviewer is invisible in judge context + report + findings.json — violates the project's 'no silent truncation' principle. Fix: thread skipped (name,reason) into the judge context and a '## Reviewers skipped' report section.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"joshuafuller@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-05-29T18:14:01Z","created_by":"Joshua Fuller","updated_at":"2026-05-29T18:30:19Z","started_at":"2026-05-29T18:30:19Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"prism-4gf.36","depends_on_id":"prism-4gf","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-05-29T13:14:01Z","created_by":"Joshua Fuller","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
